# No Tailwind `@apply`

Do **not** use Tailwind's `@apply` directive. DESIGN.md §5 surfaces are Solid components under `client/src/ui/`. Variants use [cva beta](https://cva.style/beta) (`cva@1.0.0-beta.*`) via `~/ui/cva`.

## Do

- Prefer `<Button>`, `<Field>`, `<Panel>`, `<Modal>`, `<Hud>`, `<ListRow>`, `<Felt>` from `~/ui`
- Colocate variant recipes next to the component (see `button.tsx` + `cva({...})`)
- Inline one-off chrome at the call site with `cn(...)` / JSX `class` — do not re-export shared `*Class` bags
- Put placement, size, and overrides in the JSX `class` prop

## Don't

```css
/* ❌ BAD */
.btn {
  @apply cursor-pointer rounded-control bg-llanowar;
}
```

```tsx
/* ❌ BAD — inventing a parallel class vocabulary */
export const btnClass = "…";
<button class={btnClass}>Save</button>
```

```tsx
/* ✅ GOOD */
import { Button } from "~/ui";
<Button type="button">Save</Button>
<Button variant="game-quiet" class="ml-auto">Flip</Button>
```

New surfaces: add a Solid component (and `cva` when it has variants) under `client/src/ui/` — never `@apply` in `global.css`.
